cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CYBER, cs.DL 

This paper focuses on using Twitter followers to rank universities, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves web-based artifacts and a publicly accessible Twitter API, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity). Finally, the paper also mentions using machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.DL (Deep Learning).
